description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic, motivated and innovative registered nurse to lead the established Macmillan Breast Care Nursing Team at Sandwell &amp; West Birmingham Hospitals NHS Trust. This post is a full-time position and has become available due to retirement. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will have responsibility for managing the service on a day to day basis, working together with the Lead Clinician to promote and drive forward the service. The whole team are committed to delivering the Living with and Beyond Cancer Programme for their patients.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will play a major role in developing and implementing new initiatives in line with National guidance in care and services for Breast Cancer patients within the Trust. This will involve working collaboratively with all members of the Multi-disciplinary Team to ensure excellence in patient care and service provision which focuses on patient-centred care and supports best practice.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Where appropriate the post holder will represent the nursing team at specialist meetings and forums regionally and nationally&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will be a registered professional with evidence of substantial clinical experience in breast cancer care and oncology, ongoing clinical and professional development. They should be able to demonstrate clinical leadership, both academically and in practice, as well as display strong nursing leadership qualities. A real commitment to education and teaching is also an integral part of this role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact Angie Smith&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: angie.smith4@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 0121 507 2713&lt;/p&gt;
